		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis&#44; Mo.</placeName> <date>Decbr 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5613.<add>1852</add></date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">After receipt of your favor&#44; dated <date>Oct 17th</date>&#44;<lb/> I applied to Adams Express and got your package.&#8212;<lb/>  But as I told you already in my last it is of no use<lb/> to that congregation any more and I doubt almost <sic>wether</sic><lb/> it would have been under any circumstances whatever&#59; but<lb/> this is certainly none of your fault&#44; however a proof more of<lb/> the lack of zeal and interest which our coreligionarics feel<lb/> in promoting Judaism&#44; in helping to erect houses of worship<lb/> and so on&#59;&#8212;But do you believe&#44; dear Sir&#33; That you will revive<lb/> Judaism and better the existing state of things by articles as the one<lb/> &#8222;what can be done&#8221; in your Occident No. 116.&#63;&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I wished to God almighty for the sake of our holy his defaced<lb/> and forsaken religion&#44; you would have the strength and courage<lb/> to breake the crust. that Rabbanism&#44; fanaticism&#44; hypocrisy and<lb/> Ignorance have laid around our Religion so that the Law<lb/> of <persName>Moshe</persName> and the <sic>Profets</sic> is forgotten for the abuses of middle&#45;age<lb/> and <del>that</del> through which the true heavenly light of our <add>Hebrew</add> <add>&#63;</add>can hardly penetrate.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">While on the one hand you translate the divine scriptures<lb/> on the other hand you foster their misunderstanding and misinterpreting<lb/> by articles like that &#8222;what can be done&#8221;&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Excuse my sincerity&#8212;and if our views differ&#44; believe me that<lb/> I know to respect difference of opinion&#44; though I would heartily<lb/> lament it in so far as I feel it injures the cause&#44; for which in<lb/> principle we feel alike&#44; and which I only wish and hope to see<lb/> promoted and fostered by you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I succeeded at last with some friends of the cause to write<lb/> two congregations here&#44; the Imanu El and Bne Brith<hi rend="sup">x</hi>&#8212;The new congregation<lb/> is about to organize under the s<add>&#63;</add> and title <hi rend="underline">&#8222;Bne&#45;El&#8221;</hi>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am at work to make the outlines of a constitution&#44; a<lb/> copy of which I will send you as soon as adopted.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Our means in cash on hand and Real Estate amount now<lb/> to more than two Thousand dollars&#44; and I hope that at your<lb/> next visit to <placeName>St Louis</placeName> we will be able to hear you in our<lb/> new house of Prayer and give you a better&#44; a heartfelt and<lb/> <sic>thankfull</sic> welcome.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed you will find &#36;5.00<lb/>00 for advertisement and circulars<lb/> of the late Bne Brith Congr. and I will try to make the Bne El<lb/> better patrons of your Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">with sincere respect your affectionate</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways near the bottom of the left side of the page"><hi rend="sup">x</hi> <sic>comonly</sic> called Bavarian and Bohemian Congr.</p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Editor Occident</p>
